annotationA: Proteasome subunit beta type-4; The proteasome is a multicatalytic proteinase complex which is characterized by its ability to cleave peptides with Arg, Phe, Tyr, Leu, and Glu adjacent to the leaving group at neutral or slightly basic pH. The proteasome has an ATP-dependent proteolytic activity (By similarity); Belongs to the peptidase T1B family
annotationB: Geminin, isoform A; DNA binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: eggshell chorion gene amplification; regulation of syncytial blastoderm mitotic cell cycle; endomitotic cell cycle; regulation of cell cycle; negative regulation of epidermal growth factor receptor signaling pathway; negative regulation of DNA replication
